title: Prep roundup: Big offensive numbers not enough for St. Francis football
text:
Prep roundup: Big offensive numbers not enough for St. Francis football Published: Thursday, Oct. 8, 2015 6:06 p.m. CDT By SUBURBAN LIFE MEDIA 
Nolan Pechan rushed for 170 yards and four touchdowns, Peter Fassnacht passed for 234 yards and a score, and Brett Whelton recorded 116 receiving yards and a touchdown, but all that offense wasn’t enough as St. Francis fell 49-35 against St. Laurence on Oct. 2. 
Defensively, Dan Bos tallied nine tackles and Greg Bogdanski had eight. 
The Spartans host Montini in a crucial Chicago Catholic Green game at 7:30 p.m. Oct. 9. 
FOOTBALL 
Wheaton Warrenville South 
Wheaton Warrenville South’s battered football team took another hit Oct. 2. The Tigers fell 27-0 against Waubonsie Valley, suffering their first shutout of the season in a fifth straight loss that eliminated them from playoff contention. 
Owen England rushed for 40 yards and had 45 yards receiving to lead the offense. 
WWS (1-5 overall, 1-5 DuPage Valley Conference) hosts Metea Valley on Oct. 9. 
Wheaton North 
A grueling stretch of games got even more difficult for Wheaton North’s football team Oct. 2. 
In the first of four consecutive games against teams with winning records, the Falcons fell 14-0 against Glenbard North. 
Reese Dickinson rushed for 63 yards, Luke Anthony passed for 165 yards and Steele Graham had 79 receiving yards for the Falcons. 
Wheaton North slipped to 3-3 (3-2 in the DuPage Valley Conference) before a home game against Neuqua Valley on Oct. 9. 
BOYS GOLF 
Wheaton Warrenville South 
Led by Brian McCaffrey’s 75, the Tigers finished second at the Class 3A Glenbard West regional Oct. 6 and moved on as a team to the St. Charles East sectional Oct. 12. 
Sean McCaffrey carded a 77, Justin Seymour shot a 79 and Joe Donzelli rounded out the scoring quartet with an 85. Will Rouse (86) and Benny Mulhearn (88) also played for South, which finished with a team score of 316. 
Wheaton North 
Zach Gerry shot a 76 at the Class 3A Glenbard West regional Oct. 6 to earn an at-large bid at the St. Charles East sectional Oct. 12. 
St. Francis 
The Spartans (313) finished second at the Class 2A Kaneland regional Oct. 6 and moved on to the Nazareth sectional Oct. 12. 
Jonathan Nocek and Connor Buckley each shot 77s to lead the Spartans. Ryan Keefe carded a 78 and Luke Armbrust had an 81. Conor Reinke (85) and Logan Rayburn (89) also shot well. 
Wheaton Academy 
Grant Gosden’s 75 was good for second overall, and the Warriors placed third at the Kaneland regional with a score of 320 to move on to the Nazareth sectional. Jack Dykema (80) and Kyle Bertsche (81) contributed, and Carter Bruntjen and Peter Crowe each carded 84s. Colin Anderson also played. 
GIRLS TENNIS 
Wheaton North 
The Falcons defeated Waubonsie Valley 5-2 on Oct. 1. Madeline Fidel, Marjorie Lindquist and Lily Oviatt won singles matches. Amanda Redman and Madyson Fleming and Julia Kubica and Laura Maskeri won in doubles. 
BOYS SOCCER 
Wheaton North 
The Falcons followed a 2-2 draw against Lake Park on Sept. 29 with a 1-0 win against DuPage Valley Conference-leading Glenbard North on Oct. 3. 
Wheaton Academy 
The Warriors worked quickly to dispatch Glenbard South 6-0 on Oct. 2. 
Ty Seager scored three goals to lead the way, and Isaac Anthony, Elias McCloud and Luis Rocha also scored. Wheaton Academy led 5-0 at the half. 
JD Gunn and Nathaniel Song combined for the shutout as the Warriors improved to 11-3-1 on the year.
